<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760n.61/6a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-07T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 7, 1921—5
                                        p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>61. Your 386, 387, 388, Hollyday’s 193 and 198.<note n="66" xml:id="d717fn66">None printed.</note> Report at once by cable
                            briefly your opinion as to probability of any early Bolshevik effort
                            military or peaceful to absorb Baltic States and probability of success
                            as affecting possible recognition of Esthonia and Latvia by the United
                            States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>